When reset is called with two args both containing dots (both are spec IDs), the CLI dispatches to ResetRef — a ref-edge reset. The first arg is the reviewed spec, the second is the source spec. On success, prints "Resolved ref edge: X reviewed against Y." with exit code 0. If the first arg has a dot but the second does not, the CLI rejects with a guidance message (marker-spec mismatch). Dots are the unambiguous discriminator: marker shortcodes never contain dots; spec IDs always contain exactly one dot.